params._l1Addresses: all L1 bidding addresses (to be registered onchain).
params._winnerL1: L1 bidding address of the winner.

getBiddingAddress().custom:confidential-input: a randomly created 32 byte key to be used for encryption.
getBiddingAddress().custom:emits: EncBiddingAddress(Suave sender, bidding address encrypted in bytes).
getBiddingAddress().details: If caller has no bidding address so far, create a new bidding address and/else emit it in an encrypted fashion .Assumes the secret key is freshly generated and kept confidential by the sender.This method can be called even before & after the auction.

refundNFT(address).details: calls the oracle to transfer the NFT.

params.returnAddressL1: L1 address where the NFT is to be sent to.

setUpAuction().details: Only confidentially callable by the auctioneer. Idempotent operation.

params._nftHoldingAddress: the address where the NFT must be sent to.
params.keyRecord: contains the Suave Data ID to lookup the private key in the Confidential Storage.

startAuction().details: Only confidentially callable by the auctioneer. Can only be called if the has not started yet. Calls the oracle to check if the NFT is at the nftHoldingAddress. Also checks if the end time has already passed.

claim(address).notice: Central method for all to claim their valuables. Losers get their bid back;Winner gets the NFT; Auctioneer gets the winning bid.
